    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-02T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-02T22:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8830/2310: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-03T00:00:00-03:00"
                            >April 3, 1943—midnight.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 3—3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>727. Embassy deeply appreciates arrangements made regarding newsprint for
                    importers. <hi rend="italic">El Mundo</hi> situation is precarious still and it
                    is alleging discrimination on the part Argentine shipping lines.</p>
                <p>For the Department’s information in case it is approached Embassy is advising all
                    papers that cooperation among themselves would permit of more orderly flow of
                    supplies and avoidance of the many misunderstandings which have arisen in the
                    past.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
